<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-2599] Deprecate Spatial Contrib</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2599</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;The spatial contrib is blighted by bugs.  The latest series, found by Grant and discussed &lt;a href=&quot;http://search.lucidimagination.com/search/document/c32e81783642df47/spatial_rethinking_cartesian_tiers_implementation&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; shows that we need to re-think the cartesian tier implementation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Given the need to create a spatial module containing code taken from both lucene and Solr, it makes sense to deprecate the spatial contrib, and start from scratch in the new module.&lt;/p&gt;

</description>
                <environment></environment>
            <key id="12471333">LUCENE-2599</key>
            <summary>Deprecate Spatial Contrib</summary>
